nd amended bunkers at Houston for our account and shifted last 100 mt at NYC to owners account"},{"modifiedDate":"2023-12-08T16:27:42.337","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"Houston bunkers were split with owners. Have included an expense for owners and edited the stem to show only 99.85 for our account."},{"modifiedDate":"2023-12-08T09:52:15.39","modifiedByFull":"Andersen, Thomas","remark":"Loss for BOR (same prices both ends)  result USD -80,485 / TCE USD -2,133"},{"modifiedDate":"2023-11-30T09:50:49.89","modifiedByFull":"Dragheim, Carsten Bo","remark":"Galveston LSGO Price ($/mt) updated from 903 to 918 to match the approved bunker invoice!"},{"modifiedDate":"2023-11-29T18:40:03.873","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"We are happy to see this voyage complete successfully after fear of owners not allowing the reload in Freeport! We initially thought the vessel would discharge in Savannah, however the final disport was one berth in New York, increasing freight by $95k. We had about four days on demurrage for a total of approx $141k. The discharge consumption for LSMGO was over estimated in the generation, so that saved 28 MT of LSMGO as well as idle LSMGO was estimated at 102 MT and actual was 61 MT, so we se a $25k savings in bunker costs over the entire voyage. All of these changes contribute to an improvement in the TCE and not such a loss in the final result. Port costs did increase slightly due to additional dockage at Freeport. I will also point out we had to bunker for this voyage in order to deliver the vessel per the TCP. With many changes before the fixture as well as during the voyage, it was tough to estimate the needed bunkers for redelivery and in the end once New York was confirmed as disport, we had to make an additional LSMGO order per owner\u0027s demand as we initially only bunkered enough for Savannah."},{"modifiedDate":"2023-11-29T14:34:27.117","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"The terminal charged a backloading fee"},{"modifiedDate":"2023-11-28T20:55:05.2","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"We had to bunker again in order to be in line with TCP.."},{"modifiedDate":"2023-11-28T14:59:24.817","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"Houston Port costs less than generated"},{"modifiedDate":"2023-11-20T15:24:08.36","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"Demurrage calculated"},{"modifiedDate":"2023-11-09T13:48:12.05","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"Less bunkers consumed while waiting for berth."},{"modifiedDate":"2023-11-03T01:43:43.957","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"Have to use avg hire from oct 21 to Oct 23 23:59 before hire dropped to 20000."}],"offhireList":[{"id":196553,"dateStartUtc":null,"dateEndUtc":null,"days":null,"displayOrder":0,"offhireReason":null,"remark":null,"offhireBunkerList":[{"id":228611,"gradeName":"LSBF","quantity":null,"price":null,"displayOrder":0}]}],"tcNumber":null,"tcOutIdEncrypted":null,"tcReletDetail":null}